    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/chief-credibility-officer",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The seven assessed credibility factors collectively demonstrate that the CFD hemolysis model achieves sufficient credibility for regulatory submission under the defined COU. Monte Carlo UQ confirms the 95th-percentile NIH remains 18% below the clinical threshold. The six unassessed factors are acknowledged as epistemic gaps; however, the assessment team judges that the assessed factors provide adequate aggregate evidence given the conservative UQ margin and the direct use of the COU geometry in validation. The orphan-claim risk (W-EP-01) was not flagged during internal review because the Claim node appears richly described and the ValidationResults carry full provenance chains to Evidence; the absence of a prov:wasDerivedFrom link on the Claim node itself was not detected.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
